About
I am Ibrahim Abdullahi, a graduate student of the department of Economics at Memorial University of Newfoundland and Labrador (MUN) and a research Assistant to Dr. Mustapha Immurana (Senior Research Fellow at University of Health and Allied Sciences). I also serve as a Graduate Teaching Assistant at Department of Economics MUN. I have a keen interest in Econometrics, Economic Theory, Insurance & Risks, Data Analytics, Machine learning and Causal inferences. My research span from Health economics, Labor Economics, Energy Economics, Environmental Economics and a long- standing Casual inferences
